Package: groff
Section: text
Priority: optional
Architecture: ARCH
Depends: libc (>= 1.1.8), ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: utilities for processing and formatting text
 Groff (GNU troff) is a typesetting system that reads plain text mixed 
 with formatting commands and produces formatted output. 
 .
 Output may be PostScript or PDF, html, or ASCII/UTF8 for display at the 
 terminal.

Package: groff-doc
Section: doc
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Recommends: man-db, info
Depends: groff (= ${binary:Version})
Description: documentation for Groff
 This package provides info, and man pages for Groff.
